doc.previous: Bakersfield lies around 100 miles 160 km north of Los Angeles about a 1 hour drive on I 5 and State Route 99 and about 300 mi 480 km southeast of the state capital Sacramento about a 4 hour drive on State Route 99
doc.after: Bakersfield has historically referred to its regions by directional names They are Central Bakersfield North Bakersfield Northeast East Bakersfield Southeast South Bakersfield Southwest and Northwest With the exception of Central and East Bakersfield all regions extend to the city limits East Bakersfield generally refers to the former town of Sumner later renamed East Bakersfield As a result the Northeast wraps around East Bakersfield 35
